20He%20was%20soon%20bustling%20about%20the%20room%2C%20rummaging%20among%20teacups%2C%20indicating%20the%20chairs%20we%20could%20use%2C%20amidst%20a%20flow%20of%20happy%20chatter.%20None%20of%20us%2C%20perhaps%20even%20Jayanta%20Babu%2C%20knew%20that%20he%20would%20pass%20away%20only%20a%20few%20weeks%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20poetry%20there%20is%20in%20the%20world%3Cbr%3E%20appears%20to%20rise%20out%20of%20the%20ashes.%3Cbr%3E%20The%20ash%20sits%20between%20us%20and%3Cbr%3E%20puts%20its%20arms%20across%20our%20shoulders.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20poet%20ever%20dies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20live%20Jayanta%20Mahapatra%20(1928-2023).%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FJayantaMahapatra%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23JayantaMahapatra%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FOdia%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Odia%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FPoetry%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Poetry%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FndOJjx4wtR%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FndOJjx4wtR%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Anand%20ST%20Das%20(%40anandstdas)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fanandstdas%2Fstatus%2F1695862287255715938%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2027%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20afternoon%2C%20Jatin%20Nayak%20introduced%20me%20as%20the%20grandson%20of%20a%20Communist%20Party%20member%2C%20who%20had%20passed%20away%20twenty%20years%20ago%20but%20was%20still%20fondly%20remembered%20by%20old%20timers%20in%20Odisha.%20%E2%80%9COf%20course%2C%20I%20know%20who%20that%20is%E2%80%9D%2C%20Jayanta%20Babu%20said%20of%20my%20grandfather.%20A%20rooted%20poet%2C%20he%20was%20equally%20interested%20in%20discussing%20the%20comparatively%20unspectacular%20world%20of%20Cuttack%20as%20he%20was%20describing%20his%20experiences%20at%20the%20hallowed%20International%20Writing%20Program%20at%20Iowa%2C%20where%20he%20participated%20in%20the%20year%201976-77.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahapatra%20gave%20me%20a%20piercing%20look%20and%20went%20back%20to%20his%20animated%20conversation%20with%20Nayak%20and%20his%20son%2C%20who%20was%20also%20present.%20Throughout%20the%20afternoon%2C%20Jayanta%20Babu%20never%20directed%20a%20remark%20or%20a%20question%20specifically%20towards%20me.%20But%20his%20sentences%20invited%20me%20into%20his%20conversation.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20reading%20Tolstoy%20again%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2095%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%20to%20us.%20%E2%80%9CI%20find%20I%20read%20it%20so%20differently%20today%20than%20I%20did%20decades%20ago%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20noticed%20another%20book%20that%20lay%20on%20the%20bedside%20table.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Man%20Outside%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Wolfgang%20Borchert%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20significant%20choice%20by%20Jayanta%20Babu%20that%20raised%20many%20questions%20in%20my%20mind.%20A%20nonagenarian%20poet%20reading%20the%20book%20written%20by%20a%20writer%2C%20who%20had%20died%20at%20the%20age%20of%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTr%C3%BCmmerliteratur%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20almost%20mumbled%20under%20his%20breath%2C%20giving%20the%20book%20a%20quick%20glance%2C%20while%20not%20even%20looking%20at%20me.%20Later%2C%20I%20looked%20up%20the%20word%2C%20which%20was%20the%20only%20one%20he%20said%20to%20me%20over%20an%20entire%20afternoon.%20The%20German%20term%2C%20meaning%20rubble%20literature%2C%20represented%20a%20literary%20movement%20that%20rose%20after%20World%20War%20II.%20It%20featured%20stories%20of%20loss%20and%20rejection%20%E2%80%93%20lives%20that%20had%20turned%20to%20rubble.%20But%20I%20suspected%20that%20as%20a%20poet%20and%20humanitarian%2C%20Mahapatr