y%20for%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thoughtco.com%2Fthe-history-of-foot-binding-in-china-195228%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupper%20classes%20of%20Han%20Chinese%20society%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20eventually%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fscience%2Ffootbinding%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutlawed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20now%2C%20women%20have%20been%20conditioned%20to%20believe%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsipofculture.com%2F2022%2F02%2F09%2Fhow-we-are-programmed-to-believe-that-beauty-is-pain%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeauty%20is%20pain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20pluck%20or%20shave%20their%20hair%2C%20squeeze%20their%20feet%20into%20high%20heels%2C%20or%20surgically%20enhance%20their%20anatomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E3.%20Pineapples%20were%20once%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20epitome%20of%20luxury.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221881%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22pineapple%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60b00fa102ac410018f9347a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221410%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPineapple%20is%20not%20only%20a%20delicious%20snack%2C%20but%20a%20healthy%20one%2C%20too.%3Cp%3EHuyen%20Nguyen%20%2F%20EyeEm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20250%20years%20ago%2C%20pineapples%20were%20the%20epitome%20of%20wealth%20and%20good%20breeding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201770s%2C%20these%20unlikely%20status%20symbols%20entered%20the%20zeitgeist%20to%20mean%20anything%20of%20top%20quality.%20There%20was%20no%20higher%20compliment%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-england-53432877%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Ba%20pineapple%20of%20the%20finest%20flavor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrancesca%20Beauman%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Pineapple%3A%20King%20of%20Fruits%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2Fstyle%2Fpineapples-luxury-symbol-britain%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20pineapples%20were%20sought%20after%20because%20the%20travelers%20who%20experienced%20eating%20them%20in%20the%20New%20World%20raved%20about%20their%20flavor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20fruits%20were%20so%20luxurious%20that%20they%20were%20fit%20for%20royalty.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rct.uk%2Fcollection%2F406896%2Fcharles-ii-presented-with-a-pineapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAn%20oil%20painting%20titled%20%26quot%3BCharles%20II%20Presented%20with%20a%20Pineapple%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20featured%20the%20English%20monarch%20perched%20on%20a%20terrace.%20A%20man%20%E2%80%94%20presumed%20to%20be%20John%20Rose%2C%20the%20royal%20gardener%20%E2%80%94%20kneels%20before%20him.%20He%20appears%20to%20be%20offering%20the%20royal%20a%20pineapple%2C%20then%20considered%20a%20rare%20and%20highly%20valued%20exotic%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20even%20a%20record%20of%20Charles%20II%20getting%20the%20first%20taste%20of%20the%20fruit.%20We%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20monarch%20thought%20of%20it%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rct.uk%2Fcollection%2Fthemes%2Ftrails%2Fpublic-dining-in-the-reign-of-charles-ii-1630-1685%2Fcharles-ii-presented%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Royal%20Collection%20Trust%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20record%20keeper%20was%20disappointed%20by%20the%20taste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E4.%20Mummy-unwrapping%20parties%20were%20all%20the%20rage%20in%20the%2018th%20and%2019th%20century.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20mummy%20is%20shown%20inside%20its%20large%20wodden%20sarcophagus.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63cf9f3