lture%2Fthe-strange-history-of-the-wedding-cake-1-63011094%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewidely%20available%20in%20England.%3C%2Fa%3E%20And%20the%20whiter%20the%20sugar%2C%20the%20more%20refined%20%E2%80%93%20and%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was.%20White%20icing%20on%20a%20cake%20meant%20no%20cost%20had%20been%20spared%20in%20the%20making.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20enough%2C%20pure%20white%20bridal%20cakes%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20status%2C%20Carol%20Wilson%20wrote%20in%202005%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgastronomica.org%2F2005%2F05%2F05%2Fwedding-cake-a-slice-history%2F%5C%22%3EGastronomica%20essay%20titled%20%26quot%3BWedding%20Cake%3A%20A%20Slice%20of%20History.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201840%2C%20when%20Queen%20Victoria%20married%20Prince%20Albert%2C%20the%20cake%20was%20piped%20with%20white%20icing%2C%20which%20thereafter%20was%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalgeographic.co.uk%2Fhistory-and-civilisation%2F2021%2F06%2Fqueen-victorias-300-pound-wedding-cake-set-a-big-new-trend-for-brides%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Broyal%20icing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20multi-tiered%20cake%20measured%20over%20nine%20feet%20in%20circumference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20then-Princess%20Elizabeth%20married%20Prince%20Philip%20in%201947%2C%20the%20cake%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Farts-culture%2Fthe-strange-history-of-the-wedding-cake-1-63011094%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estood%3C%2Fa%3E%20nine%20feet%20tall%20and%20weighed%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20tonne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E7.%20In%20the%20late%202010s%2C%20urban%20chickens%20became%20the%20Teslas%20of%20Silicon%20Valley's%20tech%20elite.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225365%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Indoor%20farm%20of%20hens%20that%20lay%20eggs.%20-%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e78f09a7adf7001907442c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224023%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIndoor%20farm%20of%20hens%20that%20lay%20eggs.%20-%20stock%20photo%3Cp%3EKARRASTOCK%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20an%20unusual%20fad%20gripped%20Silicon%20Valley's%20tech%20elite%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness%2Fwp%2F2018%2F03%2F02%2Ffeature%2Fthe-silicon-valley-elites-latest-status-symbol-chickens%2F%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20scions%20of%20technology%20began%20keeping%20chickens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20chicken-rearing%20has%20always%20been%20a%20mainstay%20of%20America's%20rural%20and%20working%20class%2C%20chickens%20became%20an%20unusual%20symbol%20of%20luxury%20%E2%80%94%20akin%20to%20driving%20a%20Tesla%2C%20wrote%20the%20Post's%20Peter%20Holley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20bros%20threw%20everything%20into%20their%20new%20hobby%2C%20including%20spending%20up%20to%20%2420%2C000%20for%20state-of-the-art%20coops%20and%20obsessively%20charting%20the%20color%20and%20size%20of%20the%20eggs%20laid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeslie%20Citroen%2C%20a%20chicken%20whisperer%20whose%20hourly%20consulting%20fees%20were%20%24225%20at%20the%20time%2C%20told%20the%20Post%20it%20wasn't%20uncommon%20to%20see%20these%20birds%20walk%20about%20their%20owner's%20lavish%20homes%20wearing%20diapers%20and%20roosting%20in%20bedrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20it%20shouts%20out%2C%20'These%20eggs%20did%20not%20come%20from%20Whole%20Foods%20or%20Walmart%20%E2%80%94%20these%20eggs%20came%20from%20my%20back%20yard%2C'%26quot%3B%20Citroen%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20total%20status%20symbol%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funlikely-status-symbols-history-pineapples-fake-ruins-salt-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%