n%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27170905%2FIcescape.jpeg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27170905%2FIcescape-225x300.jpeg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27170905%2FIcescape-768x1024.jpeg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670098%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIcescapes.%20Photo%3A%20Matthew%20Angus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20go%20to%20the%20office%20of%20our%20glacier%20guides%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20ahead.%20The%20unpredictable%2C%20hazardous%20conditions%20mean%20there%20is%20usually%20a%2050%25%20chance%20the%20flight%20will%20be%20cancelled.%20I%20hang%20around%2C%20waiting%20anxiously%20for%20news%2C%20then%20hear%20that%20the%20pilot%20has%20radioed-in%20the%20go-ahead.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20strictly%20forbidden%20to%20walk%20on%20the%20glacier%20without%20an%20experienced%20guide.%20Given%20the%20risks%2C%20it%20is%20incomprehensible%20why%20anyone%20should%20want%20to.%20I%20fill%20out%20a%20health%20questionnaire.%20There%E2%80%99s%20an%20embarrassing%20moment%20when%20I%20am%20weighed%20for%20the%20helicopter%20ride.%20I%20avoid%20looking%20at%20the%20scales%2C%20hoping%20the%20optimistic%20estimate%20I%20provided%20earlier%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20totally%20laughable.%20The%20guide%20tactfully%20says%20nothing%2C%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20ask.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%20the%20cheery%20guide%20kits%20me%20out%20with%20somewhat%20smelly%20waterproof%20trousers%2C%20a%20jacket%2C%20hiking%20pole%2C%20and%20crampons%2C%20after%20a%20safety%20briefing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20glacier%20drops%20steeply%20from%20the%20Southern%20Alps%20into%20a%20rainforest%2C%20so%20I%20walk%20through%20lush%20green%20vegetation%20to%20the%20airfield.%20My%20friend%E2%80%99s%20gloomy%20talk%20about%20the%20dangers%20of%20helicopters%20is%20at%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind.%20So%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20nervous%20but%20excited%20as%20the%20charismatic%20pilot%20takes%20off.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20433px)%2085vw%2C%20433px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27171149%2FDwarfed-by-giant-blue-ridges-225x300.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22433%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27171149%2FDwarfed-by-giant-blue-ridges-225x300.jpeg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27171149%2FDwarfed-by-giant-blue-ridges-768x1024.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27171149%2FDwarfed-by-giant-blue-ridges.jpeg%20900w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670099%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22577%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDwarfed%20by%20giant%20blue%20ridges.%20Photo%3A%20Matthew%20Angus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20an%20awe%20inspiring%20moment%20when%20we%20land%20on%20a%20sea%20of%20blue-white%20ice%2C%20on%20a%20patch%20no%20larger%20than%20a%20biggish%20carpet.%20I%20panic%20briefly%20when%20the%20helicopter%20takes%20off%20again%2C%20and%20I%20realise%20our%20small%20group%20is%20alone%20with%20no%20way%20down%20until%20the%20helicopter%20comes%20back.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20glacier%20guides%20have%20carved%20out%20a%20hiking%20route%2C%20with%20huge%2C%20uneven%20ice%20steps%2C%20sometimes%20requiring%20a%20rope%20to%20climb.%20It%E2%80%99s%20very%2C%20very%20slippery%20%E2%80%93%20like%20walking%20on%20a%20giant%20ice%20cube.%20I%20find%20it%20hard%20to%20relax%20or%20trust%20the%20crampons%20and%20am%20impressed%20by%20the%20speed%20at%20which%20the%20guide%20climbs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20soon%20regret%20the%20layers%20of%20clothes%20we%20were%20instructed%20to%20wear%20and%20become%20hot%20and%20sweaty%20within%20five%20minutes%20of%20walking.%20I%20find%20the%20climb%20reasonably%20strenuous%20and%20tricky%2C%20not%20being%20used%20to%20walking%20on%20ice.%20It%20takes%20about%2030%20minutes%20to%20develop%20a%20technique%20that%20works%20for%20me%20%E2%80%93%20kick%20forward%20with%20the%20spike%2C%20then%20push%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reward%20is%20dramatic%20views%20%E2%80%93%20gigantic%20icy%20pillars%2C%20deep%20blue%20ridges%2C%20and%20colossal%20ice%20caves.%20There%E2%80%99s%20unstable%20ice%20and%20deep%2C%20narrow%20crevasses%20that%20I%20quickly%20step%20over%20without%20looking%20down%2C%20fearing%20a%20vertigo%20attack.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20walk%20for%20two%20hours%20on%20the%20winding%20path%2C%20sometimes%20shuffling%20like%20caterpillars%2C%20or%20squeezing%20through%20tight%20tunnels.%20The%20highpoint%20is%20a%20pair%20of%20massive%20blue%20ridges%2C%20dwarfing%20me%20as%20I%20look%20up%2C%20moved%20to%20reverent%20silence%20by%20the%20majesty%20of%20the%20natural%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20the%20climax%20of%20my%20year%20off%2C%20and%20I%20drink%20a%20lot%20of%20wine%20that%20night%20to%20mark%20one%20of%20life%E2%80%99s%20special%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDivya%20Maitreyi%20Chari%20is%20a%20neuroscientist%20and%20Professor%20of%20Neural%20Tissue%20Engineering%20at%20the%20Keele%20School%20of%20Medicine%20in%20the%20UK.%20She%20has%20previously%20published%20articles%20on%20a%20jungle%20survival%20course%20in%20British%20Guyana%2C%20travels%20in%20Patagonia%2C%20Norway%2C%20the%20Galapagos%20islands%2C%20Southern%20Africa%20and%20along%20the%20Bhutan-Tibet%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693137697000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2