rong%3E%20UK%20prime%20minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20may%20be%20facing%20more%20troubles%20over%20his%20wife%E2%80%99s%20connection%20with%20IT%20giant%20Infosys%2C%20with%20calls%20for%20transparency%20over%20his%20interests%20as%20the%20free%20trade%20deal%20with%20India%20looks%20at%20increasing%20visas%20for%20Indian%20workers%2C%20UK%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3EObserver%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRishi%20Sunak%20faces%20a%20new%20conflict%20of%20interest%20row%20before%20a%20G20%20summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%20next%20month%20over%20claims%20that%20his%20family%20could%20stand%20to%20benefit%20financially%20from%20a%20post-Brexit%20trade%20deal%20that%20he%20is%20negotiating%20with%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Faug%2F26%2Frishi-sunak-faces-fresh-conflict-of-interest-row-over-india-trade-talks%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20newspaper%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20claimed%20that%20lawmakers%20and%20trade%20experts%20say%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20are%20concerns%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20of%20government%20over%20potential%20%E2%80%9Ctransparency%E2%80%9D%20issues%E2%80%9D%20relating%20to%20his%20wife%20Akshata%20Murty%E2%80%99s%20shareholding%20in%20Infosys.%20Akshata%20Murty%20is%20the%20daughter%20of%20one%20of%20Infosys%E2%80%99s%20founders%2C%20Narayana%20Murthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20head%20of%20the%20parliamentary%20select%20committee%20on%20business%20and%20trade%2C%20Darren%20Jones%2C%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20it%20was%20important%20for%20the%20prime%20minister%20to%20declare%20his%20interests.%20%E2%80%9CI%20expect%20him%20to%20do%20so%20in%20respect%20of%20the%20India%20trade%20deal%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Shadow%20trade%20secretary%20Nick%20Thomas-Symonds%20said%20his%20party%20backed%20a%20trade%20deal%20with%20India%20%E2%80%9Cso%20it%20is%20important%20that%20he%20%5BSunak%5D%20is%20transparent%20about%20any%20relevant%20business%20links%20and%20his%20personal%20role%20in%20negotiations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20a%20UK%20government%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20was%20pursuing%20a%20trade%20deal%20with%20India%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20United%20Kingdom%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20interests%20have%20been%20declared%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20normal%20processes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20accusation%20follows%20last%20week%E2%80%99s%20announcement%20that%20the%20UK%20parliament%E2%80%99s%20standards%20watchdog%20had%20concluded%20Sunak%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Faug%2F23%2Frishi-sunaks-actions-wifes-shareholdings-breached-mps-code-conduct%5C%22%3Ebreached%20the%20code%20of%20conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20albeit%20unintentionally.%20He%20was%20admonished%20for%20failing%20to%20properly%20declare%20his%20wife%E2%80%99s%20shareholding%20in%20a%20childcare%20company%20that%20stood%20to%20benefit%20from%20new%20government%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMurty%20was%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20another%20controversy%20last%20year%20due%20to%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2022%2Fapr%2F06%2Frishi-sunaks-wife-claims-non-domicile-status%5C%22%3Enon-domiciled%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20excludes%20her%20from%20paying%20British%20taxes%20on%20overseas%20income.%20She%20subsequently%20consented%20to%20pay%20UK%20taxes%20on%20her%20foreign%20earnings%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20prime%20minister%20will%20be%20travelling%20to%20New%20Delhi%20to%20attend%20the%20G20%20summit%20next%20month%2C%20where%20he%20is%20expected%20to%20discuss%20the%20free%20trade%20deal%20talks%20in%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%20with%20the%20host%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EObserver%3C%2Fem%3E%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aftermath%20of%20Brexit%20prompted%20the%20UK%20to%20pursue%20new%20global%20trade%20relationships%2C%20and%20a%20significant%20focus%20was%20directed%20towards%20forging%20a%20comprehensive%20trade%20pact%20with%20India.%20A%20crucial%20requirement%20put%20forth%20by%20India%20during%20the%20negotiations%20for%20a%20free-trade%20agreement%20is%20the%20expansion%20of%20visas%20granted%20to%20its%20workforce%20in%20sectors%20like%20IT%20and%20artificial%20intelligence.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20UK%20aims%20to%20secure%20reduction%20in%20tariffs%20on%20items%20such%20as%20exports%20of%20Scotch%20Whisky%20and%20automobiles%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20also%20reported%20that%20the%20UK%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20office%20has%20cautioned%20the%20parliamentary%20select%20committee%20against%20visiting%20India%20this%20year%20to%20examine%20the%20trade%20deal%20talks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20was%20advised%20by%20the%20government%20that%20it%20would%20be%20better%20to%20visit%20India%20next%20year%20instead%20of%20during%20sensitive%20trade%20negotiations%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jones%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Observer%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20foreign%20office%20informed%20that%20it%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20assist%20in%20setting%20up%20meetings%20for%20the%20committee%20members%20with%20Indian%20interlocutors.%20%E2%80%9CAmid%20signs%20of%20tension%20between%20the%20MPs%20and%20the%20FCDO%2C%20the%20committee%20will%20meet%20soon%20after%20parliament%20returns%20next%20week%20to%20discuss%20whether%20to%20go%20ahead%20anyway%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20Alan%20Manning%2C%20who%20chaired%20the%20migration%20advisory%20committee%20from%202016%20to%202019%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3EObserver%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Indian%20IT%20companies%20are%20among%20the%20biggest%20users%20of%20UK%E2%80%99s%20vis