0style%2C%20using%20a%20basic%20nib%20and%20ink%20to%20create%20mesmerising%20artworks.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EAshutosh%20Kumar%20Thakur%2C%20a%20Bengaluru-based%20management%20professional%20and%20literary%20critic%2C%20speaks%20with%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%20Santosh%20Kumar%20Das%20about%20his%20life%20and%20works%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETell%20us%20about%20your%20background%20and%20how%20did%20you%20become%20interested%20in%20Madhubani%20paintings%3F%20Can%20you%20recall%20your%20earlier%20memories%2Finfluences%20of%20holding%20the%20brush%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESantosh%20Kumar%20Das%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20originally%20come%20from%20%E2%80%98Ranti%2C%20a%20small%20village%20situated%20a%20few%20kilometres%20to%20the%20east%20of%20Madhubani.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20remember%20exactly%20when%20I%20started%20to%20paint%20and%20draw.%20Music%20and%20drawing%20have%20always%20been%20with%20me.%20Roughly%20around%20the%20age%20of%20five%2C%20I%20could%20sing%20and%20draw.%20Singing%20and%20drawing%20constantly%20occupied%20me.%20I%20remember%20my%20mother%20saying%20that%20when%20I%20could%20not%20speak%20words%2C%20I%20could%20still%20sing%20and%20hum.%20One%20of%20the%20songs%20she%20said%20I%20could%20sing%20was%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CDheere%20Chalo%20Jara%20Muqaddar%20Ki%20Gaari%20Mein%20Main%20Hum%20Do%20Anari%2C%20Ye%20Hai%20Naya%20Raasta%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%C2%A0Lata%20Mangeshkar-Subir%20Sen%20duet%20from%20%3Cem%3EAas%20Ka%20Panchhi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%201961%20Hindi%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20noted%20that%20I%20could%20not%20do%20full%20justice%20to%20the%20lyrics%20being%20a%20young%20kid%20of%20roughly%20four%20(or%20five).%20Naya%20rasta%20funnily%20became%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Nara%20Raasita%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20my%20version%20(rendition).%20Music%20and%20painting%20ran%20parallel%20in%20my%20life%20then%20and%20even%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20father%20worked%20in%20the%20railways.%20In%20my%20early%20childhood%2C%20we%20lived%20in%20Muzaffarpur%20in%20the%20railway%20colony%20near%20the%20station.%20As%20a%20child%2C%20I%20would%20pay%20several%20visits%20to%20the%20railway%20station%20in%20a%20day%20spending%20time%20looking%20at%20the%20film%20poster%20on%20the%20poles%20and%20pillars.%20A%20child%20drawing%20the%20faces%20of%20the%20matinee%20idols%20from%20those%20posters%20was%20a%20common%20sight.%20I%20would%20be%20surrounded%20by%20excited%20and%20equally%20astonished%20onlookers%20who%20showered%20gifts%20on%20me%20as%20I%20finished%20the%20sketches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20long%20have%20you%20been%20practising%20Madhubani%20painting%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Coming%20back%20to%20Mithila%20art%2C%20I%20have%20been%20painting%20since%201970%20fired%20by%20my%20own%20skills%20of%20drawing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20you%20tell%20us%20a%20bit%20about%20the%20history%20of%20Madhubani%20paintings%3F%20When%20and%20how%20did%20they%20originate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20is%20tough%20to%20put%20an%20exact%20date%20as%20to%20when%20it%20first%20began.%20However%2C%20as%20historians%20and%20writers%20have%20noted%2C%20Lord%20Ram%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20seen%20some%20murals%20adorning%20the%20walls%20of%20King%20Janak%E2%80%99s%20palace%20in%20Janakpur%2C%20now%20in%20present-day%20Nepal.%20On%20the%20cultural%20level%2C%20the%20Brahmin%20and%20Kayastha%20women%20of%20the%20Mithila%20region%20have%20been%20making%20ritualistic%20paintings%20for%20weddings%20(in%20the%20form%20of%20vermilion%20wrappers%2C%20traditionally%20carried%20by%20the%20groom%E2%80%99s%20side%20for%20the%20wedding%20to%20be%20organised%20at%20the%20bride%E2%80%99s%20place)%20and%20%E2%80%98Aripans%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20floor.%20For%20the%20wedding%2C%20a%20special%20room%20is%20earmarked%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Kohbar%20Ghar%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20walls%20and%20corners%20of%20which%20are%20richly%20painted.%20On%20the%20eastern%20wall%2C%20the%20Kohbar%20representing%20the%20lotus%20plant%2C%20symbolic%20of%20fertility%2C%20is%20painted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fewer%20words%2C%20I%20can%20say%20without%20much%20hesitation%20that%20the%20roots%20of%20this%20art%20form%20lie%20well%20within%20the%20domestic%20space%20of%20the%20Mithila%20household%20wherein%20the%20physical%20and%20the%20divine%20mingle%20to%20give%20shape%20to%20a%20unique%20cultural%20artform%20that%20later%20got%20rechristened%20as%20Madhubani%20painting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20modern%20times%2C%20Mithila%20art%20was%20first%20discovered%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20a%20natural%20disaster%20by%20a%20colonial%20officer%20named%20William%20G%20Archer.%20In%20the%20year%201934%2C%20a%20devastating%20earthquake%20measuring%208.0%20magnitude%20hit%20northern%20Bihar%20and%20neighbouring%20Nepal.%20William%20G.%20Archer%2C%20who%20was%20posted%20in%20Madhubani%20as%20an%20SDO%2C%20was%20forced%20to%20make%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20entire%20Mithila%20region.%20During%20his%20survey%2C%20what%20he%20saw%20immediately%20mesmerised%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20broken%20mud%20houses%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20Maithils%20(chiefly%20Brahmins%20and%20Kayasthas)%2C%20the%20murals%20on%20the%20outer%20and%20inner%20walls%20of%20the%20dwellings%20left%20him%20dumbfounded%20and%20he%20took%20several%20photos%20of%20these%20murals%20consisting%20of%20the%20gods%20and%20goddesses%20and%20the%20ritualistic%20wedding%20diagrams.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20time%20the%20outside%20world%20took%20notice%20of%20this%20beautiful%20tradition%20which%20had%20been%20in%20practice%20since%20the%20time%20of%20Ramayana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20after%20Independence%2C%20the%20Congress%20government%20led%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20took%20attention%20and%20thought%20of%20bringing%20this%20art%20form%20majorly%20done%20by%20women%20into%20the%20mainstream.%20Mithila%20owing%20to%20its%20geographical%20proximity%20to%20Nepal%20was%20a%20perennial%20victim%20of%20floods%20and%20droughts.%20The%20erstwhile%20Congress%20government%20sent%20the%20handicrafts%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20Mithila%20to%20create%20economic%20opportunities%20for%20the%20people%20through%20art.%20And%20the%20people%20found%20themselves%20taking%20to%20this%20traditional%20art%20with%20great%20enthusiasm%20and%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fdata-sharing-technology-art-exhibition%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Your%20Personal%20Mobile%20Number%20Is%20No%20Longer%20Yours%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20Art%20Is%20Demystifying%20Technology%20for%20the%20Masses%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20challenges%20did%20you%20face%20while%20mastering%20this%20traditional%20art%20form%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20When%20I%20first%20started%20painting%2C%20my%20mother%2C%20Savitri%20Devi%20was%20my%20first%20role%20model.%20I%20tried%20to%20paint%20in%20her%20style.%20I%20have%20told%20the%20entire%20story%20of%20my%20beginning%20in%20Madhubani%20art%20in%20a%20book%20called%20%3Cem%3EBlack%3A%20An%20Artist%E2%80%99s%20Tribute%3C%2Fem%3E%20(published%20by%20Tara%20Books%2C%20Chennai).%20In%20the%20early%20days%2C%20my%20mother%20was%20my%20muse.%20Later%20on%2C%20I%20saw%20Ganga%20Devi%E2%80%99s%20art%20in%20a%20film%20on%20Madhubani%20art%20by%20a%20French%20filmmaker%2C%20Yves%20Vequad.%20I%20at%20once%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20her%20neatness%20and%20incredibly%20powerful%20nibwork.%20Painting%20in%20the%20line%20style%2C%20discovering%20Ganga%20Devi%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20my%20artistic%20journey.%20Her%20use%20of%20black%20and%20red%20mesmerised%20me.%20My%20urge%20to%20paint%20became%20stronger.%20It%20is%20hard%20to%20believe%20what%20transpired%20in%20me.%20But%20I%20definitely%20found%20a%20direction%20I%20would%20go%20with%20my%20art%20and%20talents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27120946%2Fimage-1252.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22729%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27120946%2Fimage-1252.png%20540w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27120946%2Fimage-1252-222x300.png%20222w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670044%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22986%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20painting%20by%20Santosh%20Kumar%20Das.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20share%20a%20brief%20overview%20of%20your%20artistic%20journey%3F%20When%20and%20how%20did%20they%20originate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Well%2C%20my%20artistic%20journey%20began%20as%20early%20as%201970.%20Bhaskar%20Kulkarni%20had%20just%20introduced%20handmade%20paper%20to%20the%20village%20women%20who%20were%20used%20to%20drawing%2Fpainting%20on%20the%20walls%20and%20floors%20of%20their%20households.%20For%20I%20had%20been%20already%20drawing%20portraits%20from%20calendars%20and%20religious%20books%20(Gita%20Press%20booklets)%2C%20the%20Madhubani%20painting%20came%20easy%20for%20me.%20I%20devoted%20all%20my%20imagination%20and%20skill%20in%20creating%20beautiful%20paintings%20on%20paper.%20To%20put%20it%20more%20clearly%2C%20I%20would%20paint%20like%20an%20enthusiast%20improving%20with%20each%20painting%3B%20always%20trying%20to%20make%20the%20next%20painting%20better%20than%20the%20last%20one.%20If%20I%20started%20work%2C%20I%20would%20not%20rest%20unless%20I%20completed%20it%20as%20I%20had%20visualised%20in%20the%20beginning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20have%20been%20quite%20an%20instinctive%20person%20all%20through%20my%20life.%20This%20was%20a%20very%20exciting%20time%20with%20all%20the%20ladies%20taking%20to%20painting%20with%20great%20ardor.%20The%20arrival%20of%20painting%20in%20the%20community%20gave%20me%20an%20opportunity%20to%20develop%20my%20congenital%20talents.%20It%20continued%20in%20this%20manner%20till%20the%201980s%20began.%20In%201979%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20Delhi%20for%20a%20brief%20stint%20to%20pursue%20English%20literature%20at%20the%20university%20level%20only%20to%20return%20back%20to%20my%20village%20forced%20by%20financial%20constraints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%20began%20a%20new%20phase%20of%20my%20life.%20In%20hindsight%2C%20I%20realised%20it%20was%20destiny%20that%20did%20not%20let%20me%20succeed%20in%20my%20academic%20plans.%20Coming%20back%20to%20the%20village%2C%20I%20abandoned%20all%20fancy%20ideas%20of%20studying%20outside%20and%20thought%20of%20staying%20in%20the%20village%20and%20living%20an%20utterly%20simple%20life%20and%20pursuing%20my%20love%20for%20English%20in%20ways%20which%20were%20possible%20here.%20I%20returned%20to%20the%20same%20college%20in%20my%20hometown.%20Around%20this%20time%2C%20an%20American%20anthropologist%20named%20Raymond%20Lee%20Owens%20and%20his%20ethnomusicologist%20wife%2C%20Naomi%20Owens%2C%20came%20to%20Madhubani%20to%20research%20Madhubani%20painting.%20I%20was%20asked%20to%20join%20their%20team%20as%20a%20translator.%20The%20job%20on%20offer%20was%20to%20help%20collect%2C%20record%20and%20translate%20Mithila%20songs.%20I%20grabbed%20it%20with%20all%20my%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20lured%20me%20was%20the%20opportunity%20to%20spend%20time%20in%20the%20company%20of%20such%20great%20scholars%20that%20too%2C%20English%20speakers.%20Saying%20yes%20to%20this%20job%2C%20I%20brought%20myself%20closer%20to%20the%20culture%20and%20art%20of%20the%20region.%20I%20came%20in%20contact%20with%20painters%20across%20the%20communities.%20While%20I%20worked%20with%20them%2C%20I%20had%20the%20privilege%20of%20talking%20to%20and%20seeing%20Ganga%20Devi%2C%20the%20most%20famous%20Kayastha%20painter%20from%20very%20close%20quarters.%20Her%20works%2C%20her%20hermit-like%20personality%2C%20and%20her%20intensely%20beautiful%20paintings%20rendered%20in%20her%20characteristic%20exquisiteness%20left%20a%20strong%20mark%20on%20my%20mind%2C%20rather%20than%20my%20heart.%20Even%20though%20I%20never%20entered%20into%20a%20formal%20tutelage%2C%20she%20became%20my%20Dronacharya%2C%20my%20Guru%20in%20absentia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20work%20ended%20with%20the%20Americans%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20help%20me%20return%20to%20Delhi%20University%20to%20once%20again%20resume%20the%20same%20education%20there.%20They%20were%20so%20happy%20with%20my%20job%20as%20a%20translator%20that%20they%20were%20willing%20to%20help%20in%20all%20the%20ways%20they%20could.%20Raymond%20took%20me%20to%20Delhi%20and%20put%20me%20in%20touch%20with%20a%20few%20professors%20and%20scholars%20there%20hoping%20that%20those%20meetings%20might%20help%20me%20get%20into%20the%20University%20again.%20But%20one%20Bengali%20professor%2C%20who%20was%20also%20a%20part-time%20artist%2C%20suggested%20that%20if%20I%20could%20paint%2C%20why%20not%20pursue%20painting%20at%20an%20art%20school%20rather%20than%20study%20English%20here%3F%20He%20strongly%20advised%20me%20to%20give%20the%20artist%20in%20me%20a%20chance%20and%20lead%20an%20exciting%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaymond%20liked%20what%20that%20professor%20said.%20It%20echoed%20what%20he%20had%20dreamt%20about%20me.%20Meeting%20that%20professor%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20prophetic%20and%20set%20my%20life%20in%20a%20new%20direction.%20In%201984%2C%20Raymond%20was%20able%20to%20find%20a%20donor%20who%20would%20sponsor%20my%20education%20at%20the%20art%20school.%20A%20professor%20friend%20of%20Raymond%20from%20Denver%20agreed%20to%20finance%20me.%20In%201985%2C%20I%20joined%20the%20Faculty%20of%20Fine%20Arts%20at%20MSU%20Baroda.%20Coming%20to%20Baroda%2C%20a%20whole%20new%20world%20opened%20up%20for%20me.%20I%20was%20exposed%20to%20arts%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20But%20to%20the%20surprise%20of%20many%2C%20I%20unconsciously%20kept%20closer%20to%20my%20Madhubani%20roots%20in%20my%20art%20practice%20there.%20I%20more%20or%20less%20stayed%20away%20from%20modern%20materials%20and%20confined%20myself%20to%20pen%20drawings%20in%20black%20that%20spoke%20of%20my%20origins%20and%20my%20natural%20gifts%20of%20portraiture.%20Now%20I%20would%20say%20I%20was%20just%20responding%20to%20the%20things%20that%20spoke%20to%20me.%20Picasso%20and%20his%20freedom%20to%20express%2C%20unhindered%20and%20less%20academic%20in%20form%20appealed%20to%20me.%20I%20was%20shuttling%20between%20the%20neat%20Madhubani%20lines%20and%20the%20freakish%20forms%20rubbing%20on%20me%20from%20Picasso.%20The%20professors%20and%20the%20seniors%20looking%20at%20my%20pen%20doodles%20often%20remarked%20that%20they%20(the%20doodles)%20resemble%20the%20works%20of%20Joan%20Miro%20and%20Paul%20Klee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaroda%20proved%20to%20be%20crucial%20in%20opening%20new%20ways%20of%20seeing%20for%20me.%20I%20have%20grown%20totally%20disenchanted%20with%20Madhubani%20art.%20But%20after%20five%20years%20there%2C%20to%20my%20surprise%2C%20I%20could%20look%20at%20this%20traditional%20art%20form%20with%20new%20eyes.%20In%201990%2C%20I%20returned%20and%20began%20exploring%20the%20elements%2C%20metaphors%2C%20and%20motifs%20associated%20with%20Madhubani%20art.%20It%20was%20a%20long%20process%20that%20made%20me%20revisit%20the%20intersections%20of%20culture%2C%20myth%2C%20ritual%2C%20and%20folklore%20within%20the%20Madhubani%20idiom.%20I%20took%20to%20pen%20and%20paper%20again%2C%20started%20doodling%20and%20found%20how%20all%20the%20different%20elements%20could%20fuse%20together%20into%20a%20visual%20language%20that%20could%20accommodate%20both%20personal%20and%20cultural%20demands%20simultaneously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20decade%20after%20coming%20back%20from%20the%20Baroda%20Art%20School%2C%20I%20immersed%20myself%20completely%20in%20exploring%20how%20the%20hand-drawn%20line%20(the%20typical%20line%20made%20by%20the%20nib%20as%20represented%20in%20the%20works%20of%20the%20great%20Mithila%20painter%2C%20Ganga%20Devi)%20could%20hold%20within%20it%20the%20whole%20visual%20world%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20human%20figures%20to%20%E2%80%98Aripans(%20Alpanas)%20to%20clay%20idols%2C%20to%20Likhua-Padhua%20(the%20intricately%20made%20Urad-Besan%20savouries%20that%20was%20primarily%20part%20of%20the%20wedding%20(feast)%20menu%2C%20etc.%20My%20innermost%20belief%20was%20that%20the%20line%20defines%2C%20shapes%2C%20characterises%20everything%20seen%20in%20the%20whole%20world.%20My%20urge%20to%20see%20the%20world%20in%20the%20traditional%20Madhubani%20style%20constantly%20engaged%20me%2C%20forcing%20me%20to%20draw%20and%20paint%20themes%20not%20very%20popular%20amidst%20the%20community%20of%20artists%20living%20around%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWho%20could%20have%20thought%20that%20child%20games%20like%20%E2%80%98Ghughua%20Manna%20Upje%20Dhanna%E2%80%99%20could%20have%20a%20visual%20life%20of%20its%20own%3F%20I%20was%20doing%20all%20this%20in%20the%20early%201990s.%20All%20those%20drawings%20were%20bought%20by%20the%20Japanese%20collector%20Tokio%20Hasegawa.%20He%20promised%20that%20these%20works%20shall%20go%20into%20the%20Mithila%20Museum%20which%20he%20had%20just%20founded%20in%20Niigata%2C%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hard%20work%20of%20the%2090s%20reinforced%20faith%20in%20my%20decision%20to%20return%20to%20Mithila%20Art%20despite%20having%20gone%20to%20an%20art%20school.%20This%20decision%20was%20not%20an%20easy%20one%20to%20carry%20off.%20The%20community%20was%20busy%20churning%20out%20reproductions%20of%20things%20that%20sold%20without%20much%20difficulty.%20%C2%A0I%20would%20only%20take%20up%20themes%20that%20had%20a%20personal%20appeal.%20Painting%20revolved%20around%20consolidating%20a%20proper%20understanding%20of%20the%20Madhubani%20style%20with%20an%20emphasis%20on%20the%20technique%20and%20treatment.%20By%20honestly%20applying%20myself%20to%20the%20Mithila%20medium%20and%20mastering%20its%20various%20elements%20through%20practice%2C%20in%20my%20mind%2C%20I%20began%20to%20rise%20above%20all%20the%20petty%20divisions%20of%20classical%2C%20folk%20or%20modern.%20Painting%20in%20the%20traditional%20style%20now%20was%20no%20less%20an%20inferior%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECome%20the%20new%20millennium%2C%20Raymond%20(sadly%20this%20is%20the%20only%20word%20that%20immediately%20came%20to%20my%20mind)%20again%20made%20a%20comeback%20in%20my%20life.%20He%20was%20seeing%20me%20after%20a%20decade%20and%20a%20half.%20I%20had%20very%20little%20correspondence%20with%20him%20since%20I%20joined%20the%20art%20school%20and%20he%20left%20for%20America.%20He%20was%20so%20happy%20to%20see%20that%20I%20still%20carried%20the%20same%20love%20and%20passion%20for%20art%20and%20had%20done%20well%20in%20my%20own%20right.%20He%20saw%20my%20paintings%20and%20the%20only%20piece%20of%20advice%20he%20gave%20me%20was%20to%20supersize%20my%20works.%20He%20was%20very%20impressed%20with%20the%20use%20of%20neat%20lines%20and%20designs.%20The%20line%20style%20was%20witnessing%20a%20certain%20shift%20of%20loyalty%20in%20its%20practitioners.%20The%2090s%20market%20made%20the%20boundaries%20between%20blurs.%20But%20I%20still%20kept%20painting%20in%20the%20line%20style%20in%20all%20its%20dignity%20and%20essence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20began%20working%20with%20a%20greater%20urge%20and%20vigour.%20The%20beginning%20of%20the%20new%20millennium%20saw%20me%20entering%20into%20large%20panels%20depicting%20folk%20stories%20rendered%20in%20the%20wonderful%20line%20style%20of%20Madhubani.%20The%20panels%20describing%20the%20story%20of%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Hansraj%20and%20Bachraj%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20story%20I%20heard%20from%20my%20mother%20in%20my%20childhood%20are%20a%20prestigious%20part%20of%20the%20Art%20Institute%20of%20Chicago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20after%20the%20horrific%20communal%20riots%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20the%20reports%20of%20killings%20of%20Muslims%20as%20well%20as%20Hindus%20started%20to%20spread%20through%20newspapers%20and%20television.%20I%20was%20greatly%20shocked%20at%20the%20turn%20of%20events%20that%20shook%20the%20whole%20nation.%20On%20a%20personal%20note%2C%20I%20was%20emotionally%20hurt%20as%20I%20had%20a%20special%20bond%20with%20Gujarat.%20Overcome%20by%20grief%2C%20I%20thought%20of%20capturing%20the%20riots%20in%20the%20Madhubani%20style%20%E2%80%93%20initially%2C%20it%20seemed%20too%20daunting%20a%20task%20especially%20as%20there%20had%20been%20no%20such%20depiction%20in%20this%20style%20before.%20I%20did%20a%20series%20of%2024%20paintings%20highlighting%20the%20death%20of%20human%20values%2C%20the%20death%20of%20Gandhism%20and%20the%20death%20of%20secularism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20one%20of%20my%20American%20friends%2C%20David%20Szanton%20(a%20close%20friend%20of%20Raymond%20Owens%20%E2%80%93%20with%20whom%20he%20had%20floated%20an%20art%20organisation%20called%20EAF%20in%20the%20US%20that%20focused%20on%20the%20marketing%20and%20appreciation%20for%20Mithila%20Art%20and%20a%20committed%20academic%20who%20has%20curated%20shows%20on%20Mithila%20art%20extensively%20across%20US%20and%20Europe%2C%20and%20has%20also%20published%20a%20number%20of%20papers%20on%20Mithila%20art%20in%20prestigious%20publications%20across%20the%20world)%20saw%20them%20and%20was%20mesmerised%20by%20such%20beautiful%20handling%20of%20a%20subject%20as%20unusual%20as%20riots%20in%20this%20folk%20style.%20He%20took%20them%20to%20the%20US.%20Eventually%2C%20in%202005%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20travelling%20to%20a%20number%20of%20cities%20in%20the%20US%2C%20India%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20Mexico%20as%20part%20of%20an%20exhibition%20titled%20%E2%80%98Edge%20of%20Desire%3A%20Recent%20Art%20in%20India%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20David%20Szanton%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20sudden%20demise%20of%20Raymond%20Owens%2C%20I%20joined%20an%20art%20school%2C%20Mithila%20Art%20Institute%20in%20Madhubani%20as%20its%20first%20teacher-cum-director.%20For%20five%20years%2C%20I%20taught%2030%20students%20(per%20year)%20the%20basics%20of%20Madhubani%20painting%2C%20the%20principles%20of%20drawing%2C%20the%20technique%2C%20and%20the%20designs%20%E2%80%93%20in%20brief%2C%20every%20department%20associated%20with%20the%20Madhubani.%20The%20school%20was%20very%20successful%20as%20we%20were%20able%20to%20impart%20cultural%20awareness%20and%20technical%20proficiency%20to%20the%20young%2C%20modern%20Maithil%20boys%20and%20girls.%20In%20the%20five%20years%20I%20worked%20at%20the%20institute%2C%20it%20acquired%20a%20strong%20reputation%20as%20a%20centre%20of%20learning%20and%20Mithila%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20journey%20so%20far%20has%20been%20very%20diverse.%C2%A0%20Nowadays%2C%20I%20am%20mostly%20painting%20from%20my%20home%20studio%20in%20the%20village.%20My%20journey%20would%20not%20have%20been%20the%20same%20had%20it%20not%20been%20for%20one%20individual%2C%20my%20nephew%2C%20Shantanu%20Das.%20He%20has%20always%20been%20there%20with%20me%20from%20a%20very%20young%20age.%20We%20live%20in%20a%20joint%20family.%C2%A0%20Shantanu%20has%20been%20there%20like%20a%20shadow%20to%20everything%20that%20I%20have%20done%20in%20the%20arts%20since%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20quit%20the%20Mithila%20Art%20School%20in%20Madhubani%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20devote%20all%20my%20time%20to%20the%20artist%20inside%20which%20was%20crying%20for%20my%20time%20and%20attention.%20I%20began%20painting%20with%20the%20same%20youthful%20fervour%2C%20painting%20everything%20that%20engaged%20my%20imagination.%20I%20painted%20a%20long%20series%20of%20paintings%20depicting%20the%20exploits%20of%20Lord%20Krishna%20and%20a%20series%20on%20yoga%20and%20different%20postures.%20I%20am%20a%20lover%20of%20arts%20of%20all%20kinds%20%E2%80%93%20be%20it%20music%2C%20dance%20or%20cinema.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENowadays%2C%20I%20am%20painting%20mostly%20in%20black%20and%20a%20bit%20of%20red.%20From%20a%20very%20young%20age%2C%20I%20am%20deeply%20influenced%20by%20the%20lives%20and%20teachings%20of%20mystics%2C%20saints%20and%20seers%20of%20India.%20I%20have%20a%20special%20connection%20with%20Buddha%20and%20his%20teachings.%20There%20is%20a%20strong%20reflection%20of%20all%20these%20on%20my%20art%20and%20my%20life%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20challenges%20did%20you%20face%20while%20mastering%20this%20art%20form%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20never%20had%20challenges%2C%20especially%20those%20of%20the%20artistic%20kind.%20I%20have%20always%20been%20doing%20art%20from%20a%20very%20young%20age.%20And%20it%20has%20been%20a%20permanent%20character%20of%20my%20life.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20have%20understood%20life%20and%20the%20bigger%20questions%20around%20it%20through%20art.%20So%2C%20I%20never%20found%20any%20difficulty%20in%20drawing%20and%20painting.%20When%20it%20came%20to%20art%2C%20I%20was%20never%20in%20a%20hurry.%20I%20always%20approached%20it%20with%20all%20my%20passion%20and%20devoted%20as%20much%20time%20as%20I%20could%20manage.%20Even%20as%20a%20young%20boy%2C%20I%20would%20not%20relax%20till%20my%20painting%20would%20be%20complete.%20I%20have%20that%20natural%20perseverance%20and%20concentration%20required%20for%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20challenge%20I%20think%20I%20faced%20was%20how%20to%20restrain%20myself%20and%20retain%20focus%20on%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do.%20The%20market%20can%20be%20a%20distraction%20and%20it%20can%20often%20trap%20you%20into%20a%20cycle%20of%20repetition.%20And%20that%20could%20mean%20death%20for%20an%20artist%20who%20wants%20to%20keep%20growing%20and%20finding%20new%20directions%20for%20his%20imagination%20and%20skill.%20I%20am%20lucky%20I%20always%20had%20that%20rootedness%20and%20self-belief%20that%20kept%20me%20tied%20to%20my%20own%20natural%20talents%20and%20the%20activities%20my%20heart%20believed%20in.%20I%20have%20never%20run%20after%20money.%20I%20have%20rather%20earned%20it%20after%20investing%20decades%20in%20learning%20art.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20believe%20in%20any%20shortcuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27121119%2Fimage-1253.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22752%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27121119%2Fimage-1253.png%20552w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27121119%2Fimage-1253-225x300.png%20225w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670045%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221003%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20painting%20by%20Santosh%20Kumar%20Das.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20the%20Madhubani%20painting%20reflect%20the%20cultural%20heritage%20and%20traditions%20of%20your%20region%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Madhubani%20painting%20has%20its%20very%20roots%20in%20the%20everyday%20rituals%20and%20festivals%20observed%20in%20a%20calendar%20year.%20In%20weddings%2C%20the%20painting%20was%20a%20key%20ingredient%20that%20appeared%20prominently%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98Khobar%20Room%E2%80%99%20and%20also%20as%20a%20decoration%20of%20the%20household.%20The%20painting%20is%20the%20meeting%20ground%20of%20all%20the%20different%20elements%20of%20the%20culture.%20The%20sources%20are%20so%20varied.%20Yet%20they%20all%20find%20their%20place%20in%20the%20traditional%20painting.%20Mithila%E2%80%99s%20cuisine%20is%20so%20much%20dominated%20by%20the%20fish%20motif%20which%20also%20figures%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98Vamacara%E2%80%99%20Tantra%20practice.%20Even%20in%20the%20wedding%2C%20a%20fisherwoman%20is%20expected%20to%20show%20up%20with%20fish%20%E2%80%93%20a%20sight%20that%20is%20believed%20to%20give%20an%20auspicious%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20Mithila%2C%20one%20would%20be%20so%20surprised%20to%20see%20the%20number%20of%20ponds%20punctuating%20the%20area.%20The%20culture%20is%20based%20on%20the%20human%20ties%20with%20nature%20and%20the%20Madhubani%20tradition%20reflects%20just%20that.%20Culturally%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20form%20of%20visual%20literacy%20%E2%80%93%20one%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20tap%20into%20one%E2%80%99s%20creativity.%20And%20in%20the%20case%20of%20women%2C%20culture%20makes%20the%20physical%20space%20more%20interesting%2C%20and%20they%20own%20it%20with%20their%20creative%20endeavours.%20Painting%20is%20just%20a%20small%20part%20of%20that%20rich%20cultural%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20motifs%20are%20commonly%20used%20in%20your%20Madhubani%20works%3F%20Could%20you%20briefly%20tell%20us%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20my%20works%2C%20parrots%20have%20a%20strong%20presence.%20They%20come%20directly%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98Kohbar%E2%80%99%20painting%20which%20symbolises%20love.%20In%20the%20Maithili%20language%2C%20it%20is%20called%20%E2%80%98Latpatiya%20Suga%E2%80%99%20(intertwined%20parrots).%20Fish%20is%20also%20a%20motif%20I%20have%20used%20a%20lot.%20Sometimes%20I%20use%20them%20in%20the%20exact%20context%20as%20dictated%20by%20the%20tradition.%20Sometimes%20I%20also%20add%20my%20own%20meaning%20depending%20on%20the%20way%20I%20choose%20to%20present%20them.%20On%20that%20note%2C%20parrots%20are%20a%20love%20symbol.%20But%20I%20have%20also%20used%20them%20as%20symbols%20of%20freedom%20or%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fmadhubani-bihar-contraception-reproductive-health%5C%22%3ESurreptitiously%20Seeking%20a%20Change%20in%20Madhubani%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20would%20you%20describe%20your%20unique%20style%20within%20the%20realm%20of%20Madhubani%20art%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20My%20style%20is%20very%20distinct.%20Fundamentally%2C%20it%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20line%20style%20of%20Madhubani%20art.%20What%20I%20strive%20for%20in%20my%20painting%20is%20the%20purity%20of%20form%20and%20drawing.%20The%20application%20of%20designs%20and%20patterns%20to%20distinguish%20a%20character%20or%20emotion%20or%20feeling%20has%20to%20be%20very%20fluid%20and%20musical.%20Physically%2C%20my%20paintings%20are%20a%20mix%20of%20my%20own%20visual%20memories%20and%20the%20cultural%20overtones%20that%20I%20imbibe%20from%20them.%20It%20is%20all%20actually%20a%20very%20instinctive%20process%3B%20particularly%20hard%20to%20put%20in%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20traditional%20materials%20you%20use%20for%20Madhubani%20painting%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Madhubani%20painting%20is%20basically%20done%20with%20the%20most%20basic%20of%20tools.%20The%20colours%20when%20I%20first%20started%20in%20the%201970s%20were%20all%20handmade.%20The%20black%20colour%20was%20initially%20made%20with%20the%20juice%20squeezed%20out%20of%20leaves%20from%20the%20runner%20bean%20creepers%20that%20would%20be%20fixed%20gum.%20To%20get%20the%20right%20thickness%20one%20would%20add%20water.%20This%20black%20%5Bcolour%5D%20would%20not%20last%20long%20and%20would%20turn%20a%20pinkish%20shade%20only%20to%20fade%20quickly.%20We%20have%20tried%20making%20black%20colour%20with%20the%20oxide%20powder%20bought%20from%20the%20market.%20This%20powder%20was%20boiled%20with%20gum%20in%20water.%20This%20was%20a%20little%20better%20than%20the%20first%20one.%20It%20lasted%20a%20little%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2080s%2C%20we%20all%20switched%20to%20the%20easier%20option%2C%20that%20is%2C%20the%20drawing%20ink%20in%20bottles%20made%20by%20companies%20like%20Camlin.%20Towards%20the%20new%20millennium%2C%20people%20started%20using%20acrylic%20colours%20as%20acid-free%20paper%20came%20into%20fashion.%20The%20line%20style%20uses%20a%20minimum%20of%20tools.%20All%20you%20need%20is%20a%20pen%20and%20a%20nib%20tucked%20on%20one%20end.%20My%20tools%20and%20materials%20are%20the%20same%20as%20others.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20paper%20I%20have%20been%20using%20for%20the%20last%2010%20years%20is%20not%20something%20I%20can%20buy%20in%20the%20local%20market.%20I%20have%20to%20import%20it%20from%20Delhi%2C%20or%20I%20pick%20up%20paper%20when%20travelling%20to%20bigger%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20you%20briefly%20explain%20the%20techniques%20involved%20in%20creating%20a%20Madhubani%20artwork%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20technique%20involved%20is%20simple.%20We%20all%20start%20by%20drawing%20out%20the%20composition%20on%20paper.%20Most%20of%20the%20artists%20first%20use%20a%20pencil%20to%20eke%20out%20the%20draft.%20Personally%2C%20I%20believe%20in%20first-hand%20drawing%20in%20colour%20using%20a%20dip%20pen.%20And%20then%20steepling%20or%20hatching%20comes%20into%20play.%20The%20last%20part%20is%20the%20decoration%20or%20design%20of%20the%20spaces%20and%20clothes%20or%20other%20adornments.%20If%20it%20is%20line%20style%2C%20we%20have%20to%20deal%20mostly%20in%20two%20colours%2C%20namely%2C%20black%20and%20red.%20The%20designs%20in%20the%20line%20style%20are%20mostly%20intricate%20and%20a%20bit%20subtle%20as%20compared%20to%20colour%20style%2C%20where%20forms%20and%20surfaces%20are%20bolder.%20Once%20the%20characters%20and%20background%20are%20taken%20care%20of%2C%20the%20painting%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20complete.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20inspires%20your%20creativity%20when%20starting%20a%20new%20Madhubani%20project%3F%20Are%20there%20any%20particular%20stories%20or%20cultural%20elements%20that%20often%20find%20their%20way%20into%20your%20artworks%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20If%20it%20is%20a%20personal%20project%2C%20it%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20an%20idea%20or%20an%20image%20my%20mind%20is%20engaged%20with%20at%20that%20very%20moment.%20I%20can%20often%20see%20the%20final%20painting%20in%20my%20mind%E2%80%99s%20eye.%20Once%20I%20set%20out%20to%20give%20shape%20to%20it%2C%20I%20follow%20my%20plan%20inch%20by%20inch.%20In%20case%20things%20are%20not%20working%20out%2C%20I%20let%20it%20grow%20organically.%20I%20start%20working%20on%20the%20face%20and%20gradually%2C%20the%20picture%20of%20the%20torso%20starts%20to%20get%20clearer%20in%20my%20mind.%20Then%20the%20rest%20follows%20in%20sync.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20is%20a%20commissioned%20project%2C%20I%20can%20work%20on%20the%20brief%20shared.%20Else%20I%20can%20work%20on%20a%20draft%20thinking%20what%20may%20suit%20the%20client.%20To%20an%20extent%2C%20the%20process%20remains%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20choose%20the%20colour%20palette%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20For%20me%20choosing%20the%20colours%20is%20never%20a%20fuss.%20Black%20for%20me%20is%20the%20colour%20that%20gives%20form%20to%20my%20paintings.%20Black%20is%20the%20body%2C%20Red%20is%20the%20prana%2C%20the%20energy%20of%20being.%20A%20tiny%20bit%20of%20red%20and%20the%20black%20begins%20to%20move%20in%20the%20frame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20using%20colours%2C%20I%20follow%20my%20instincts%20and%20ascribe%20them%20to%20my%20memories%20of%20those%20colours.%20Like%20the%20orange%20of%20a%20mango%20seen%2025%20years%20back%20can%20inspire%20me%20to%20take%20up%20orange%20at%20this%20very%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20most%20rewarding%20aspects%20of%20being%20a%20Madhubani%20artist%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20is%20hard%20to%20pinpoint%20one.%20But%20what%20immediately%20stands%20out%20for%20me%20is%20the%20facility%2C%20the%20sense%20of%20belonging%20it%20gives%20to%20you%20to%20express%20yourself.%20It%20gives%20you%20the%20same%20feeling%20as%20speaking%20in%20your%20mother%20tongue.%20I%20personally%20don%E2%80%99t%20attach%20much%20value%20to%20the%20labels%20of%20folk%20or%20modern.%20For%20me%2C%20art%20is%20a%20result%20of%20observation%20and%20experience.%20While%20pursuing%20art%20with%20honesty%20and%20spontaneity%2C%20it%20can%20open%20you%20to%20the%20infinite%20possibilities%20embedded%20within%20itself.%20Practice%20is%20the%20key.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20what%20ways%20do%20you%20actively%20promote%20and%20preserve%20the%20Madhubani%20painting%20tradition%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Madhubani%20painting%2C%20in%20my%20opinion%2C%20is%20a%20social%20art.%20Painting%20for%20the%20market%20is%20pretty%20recent.%20By%20doing%20art%20in%20the%20best%20possible%20way%2C%20by%20practicing%20the%20art%20form%20in%20the%20most%20refined%20way%2C%20I%20think%20I%20am%20doing%20a%20great%20service%20to%20the%20culture%20of%20the%20land.%20What%20you%20achieve%20through%20your%20efforts%20becomes%20the%20message%20for%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20conduct%20workshops%20or%20teach%20the%20art%20form%20to%20others%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20have%20done%20workshops%20in%20the%20past.%20But%20now%2C%20I%20only%20accept%20senior%20students%20who%20want%20to%20learn%20Madhubani%20painting%20in%20a%20deeper%2C%20freer%20way%20without%20any%20concern%20for%20time.%20I%20also%20give%20WhatsApp%20lessons%20to%20a%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20age%20of%20smartphones%20and%20computers%2C%20Madhubani%20painting%20is%20spreading%20far%20and%20wide%2C%20to%20very%20unlikely%20places.%20We%20often%20see%20a%20non-Maithil%20eager%20to%20learn%20and%20practice%20this%20art.%20The%20major%20change%20is%20the%20internet%20where%20you%20can%20find%20out%20things%20that%20can%20aid%20your%20learning.%20It%20has%20also%20resulted%20in%20duplicity.%20That%20is%20a%20little%20sad.%20But%20then%2C%20these%20things%20will%20happen.%20We%20need%20to%20stay%20positive%20and%20work%20hard%20as%20artists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20see%20any%20major%20change%20in%20Madhubani%20paintings%20in%20recent%20times%3F%20Is%20a%20traditional%20Madhubani%20painting%20different%20from%20a%20modern%20one%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20this%20globalised%20world%2C%20it%20is%20easier%20to%20confuse%20oneself%20with%20baseless%20and%20alien%20ideas%20of%20modernity.%20The%20youngsters%20are%20natural%20prey%20to%20such%20ideas.%20In%20my%20years%20as%20a%20teacher-director%20at%20Mithila%20Art%20Institute%2C%20I%20can%20say%20I%20was%20able%20to%20bring%20youth%20from%20all%20castes%20and%20communities%20under%20one%20roof%20to%20explore%20and%20learn%20Madhubani%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201990s%2C%20some%20revolutionary%20changes%20happened%20to%20Madhubani%20painting.%20The%20prevailing%20traditional%20styles%20became%20more%20fluid%2C%20and%20the%20boundaries%20of%20the%20colour%20and%20the%20line%20started%20to%20blur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20believe%20that%20Madhubani%20art%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20bring%20about%20social%20change%20or%20raise%20awareness%20on%20certain%20issues%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Art%20does%20have%20the%20power%20to%20bring%20change.%20The%20best%20it%20could%20have%20done%20for%20Mithila%20society%20is%20to%20present%20an%20economic%20opportunity%20that%20could%20bring%20succour%20to%20the%20land%20subjected%20to%20political%20apathy%2C%20natural%20disasters%2C%20and%20economic%20abjectness.%20More%20than%20creating%20immediately%20recognisable%20changes%2C%20it%20can%20create%20social%20and%20cultural%20awareness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20ever%20used%20your%20art%20to%20convey%20a%20particular%20message%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20My%20own%20series%20on%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots%20was%20a%20response%20to%20the%20social%20and%20political%20upheavals%20in%20the%20country.%20From%20time%20immemorial%2C%20art%20has%20provided%20a%20mirror%20to%20society%20creating%20relevant%20debates%20around%20culture%20and%20history.%20These%20days%2C%20Madhubani%20paintings%20have%20done%20well%20in%20highlighting%20social%20issues%20like%20female%20infanticide%20and%20dowry%20deaths.%20Cultural%20awareness%20is%20at%20the%20root%20of%20all%20human%20creation%20I%20believe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-bihar-madhubani-library-urdu-literature%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20in%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20Madhubani%2C%20the%20Story%20of%20a%20Library%20Reflects%20the%20Dying%20Nature%20of%20Urdu%20in%20the%20Region%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETell%20us%20a%20bit%20about%20painters%20from%20Mithila%20belonging%20to%20non-Brahman%2F%E2%80%99upper%E2%80%99%20caste%2C%20Dalit%20and%20Muslim%20(minorities)%20communities%20who%20have%20enriched%20Madhubani%20painting%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20good%20question.%20I%20am%20thankful%20to%20you%20for%20putting%20it%20across.%20The%20non-Brahman%20Or%20Dalit%20painters%20in%20popular%20parlance%20belong%20to%20two%20main%20genres.%20Harijan%20art%2C%20Godana%20art.%20Both%20styles%20are%20practiced%20by%20the%20Dalit%20women.%20The%20harijan%20style%20is%20a%20bold%20expression%20that%20uses%20dots%20in%20the%20outlines%20and%20figures.%20It%20was%20mainly%20done%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20houses.%20And%20%E2%80%98Godana%20Art%E2%80%99%20basically%20drew%20upon%20the%20forms%20found%20in%20the%20tattoos%20on%20the%20body%20of%20women%20representing%20paddy%20fields%2C%20flowers%2C%20mythical%20birds%2C%20spice%2C%20and%20elephants.%20When%20the%20Dalit%20women%20(especially%20from%20the%20Dussadh%20caste)%20were%20encouraged%20by%20Dr%20Erika%20Moser%2C%20a%20German%20Anthropologist%20to%20transfer%20these%20images%20on%20paper%2C%20Godana%20art%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20many%20great%20painters.%20Chano%20Devi%2C%20Uttam%20Paswan%2C%20Swarup%20Lal%20Paswan.%20Lalita%20Devi%20and%20Urmila%20Devi%20to%20name%20a%20few.%20The%20presence%20of%20such%20diverse%20artistic%20voices%20alongside%20the%20upper%20caste%2C%20Brahman%20and%20Kayastha%20painters%20speak%20of%20a%20very%20cohesive%2C%20syncretic%20culture%20of%20Mithila.%20My%20favorite%20was%20Jamuna%20Devi.%20She%20painted%20in%20the%20harijan%20style.%20Her%20paintings%20on%20the%20life%20of%20chamars(the%20blacksmiths)%20are%20exemplary%20of%20how%20art%20can%20document%20social%20realities%2C%20and%20can%20also%20provide%20a%20lens%20through%20which%20society%20can%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20the%20current%20generation%20of%20Dalit%20painters%2C%20Naresh%20Paswan%20and%20Shrawan%20Paswan%20stand%20out%20prominently.%20These%20are%20two%20artists%20who%20possess%20great%20skill%20and%20strong%20powers%20of%20storytelling.%20The%20unique%20feature%20of%20these%20artists%20is%20that%20they%20are%20quite%20fluid%20over%20caste%20lines.%20Shrawan%20especially%20can%20work%20in%20both%20styles%2C%20in%20the%20upper%20caste%20Mithila%20style%20that%20uses%20sophisticated%20lines%20and%20colour%20as%20well%20as%20the%20more%20playful%20Godana%20style.%20Naresh%20limits%20himself%20to%20paintings%20done%20in%20black%20colour%20and%20has%20a%20very%20sensible%20take%20on%20issues%20around%20caste%20and%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Dalit%20art%20in%20Mithila%20does%20not%20have%20a%20long%20history.%20But%20in%20a%20short%20span%20of%20time%2C%20it%20has%20grown%20strongly%2C%20mixing%20social%20critique%20and%20folklore%20to%20lure%20the%20art%20world%20globally.%20I%20won%E2%80%99t%20hesitate%20to%20say%20that%20the%20presence%20of%20such%20diverse%20voices%20both%20upper%20caste%20and%20Dalit%20vouch%20for%20the%20inclusive%20nature%20of%20our%20socio-cultural%20ecosystem%20where%20social%20interaction%20across%20caste%20and%20religion%20is%20embedded%20in%20the%20culture%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Mithila%20region%20of%20Bihar%2C%20a%20remarkable%20shift%20is%20occurring%20as%20Muslim%20girls%20embrace%20the%20art%20form%20of%20Madhubani%20painting.%20This%20art%20form%20is%20now%20being%20explored%20by%20these%20girls%2C%20challenging%20long-held%20taboos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20realm%20of%20traditional%20Madhubani%20painting%2C%20a%20group%20of%20Muslim%20women%20is%20making%20their%20presence%20felt.%20Among%20them%20are%20prominent%20voices%20like%20Sarvari%20Begum%2C%20Rehmati%20Khatoun%2C%20and%20Shazia%20Sheikh.%20They%20have%20also%20trained%20under%20teachers%20from%20the%20Hindu%20community%20and%20are%20driven%20to%20represent%20social%20issues%2C%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20through%20their%20artwork.%20All%20of%20them%20are%20young%20trying%20to%20break%20away%20from%20religious%20restrictions%20in%20order%20to%20use%20art%20as%20a%20means%20of%20social%20awareness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20participated%20in%20any%20art%20exhibitions%2C%20either%20locally%20or%20internationally%3F%20What%20are%20some%20of%20your%20notable%20achievements%20as%20a%20Madhubani%20artist%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYes%2C%20I%20have%20taken%20part%20in%20exhibitions.%20At%20the%20local%20level%2C%20due%20to%20the%20dearth%20of%20patrons%20and%20entrepreneurs%2C%20there%20are%20no%20exhibitions%20taking%20place.%20But%20I%20do%20participate%20in%20national%20and%20international%20exhibitions.%20For%20the%20last%2010%20years%2C%20I%20have%20been%20working%20constantly%20with%20a%20Delhi-based%20gallery%2C%20Ojas%20Art.%20Ojas%20Art%20is%20probably%20the%20first%20private%20organization%2Fgallery%20that%20solely%20works%20in%20the%20field%20of%20the%20folk%20and%20tribal%20arts.%20It%20keeps%20conducting%20shows%20of%20my%20art.%20It%20has%20been%20a%20wonderful%20association%20and%20hope%20that%20continues%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20notable%20achievement%20is%20that%20I%20have%20been%20able%20to%20devote%20my%20whole%20life%20to%20art.%20Despite%20a%20bleak%20local%20scene%20and%20conservative%20attitudes%20shown%20by%20the%20community%2C%20I%20have%20continued%20my%20work%20from%20my%20frugal%20home%20studio%20in%20the%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20your%20future%20goals%20and%20aspirations%20as%20an%20artist%3F%20Are%20there%20any%20new%20directions%20or%20experiments%20you%20want%20to%20explore%20within%20the%20realm%20of%20Madhubani%20art%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20only%20goal%20is%20to%20keep%20painting%20till%20my%20last%20breath.%20This%20is%20the%20only%20wish%20I%20have%20standing%20at%20the%20juncture%20I%20am%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20I%20would%20like%20to%20do%20more%20illustrations%20for%20books%2C%20particularly%20children%E2%80%99s%20books.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20I%20have%20once%20done%20my%20autobiography%20in%20the%20Madhubani%20style%20which%20was%20published%20by%20Tara%20Books%2C%20Chennai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20advice%20would%20you%20give%20to%20young%20artists%20who%20wish%20to%20pursue%20Madhubani%20painting%20or%20traditional%20art%20forms%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESKD%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMy%20advice%20to%20young%20artists%20is%20simple.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20go%20for%20shortcuts%20if%20you%20want%20to%20seriously%20learn%20art.%20Art%2C%20specifically%2C%20demands%20greater%20honesty%20and%20patience.%20These%20are%20the%20two%20qualities%20that%20can%20help%20you%20apply%20yourself%20appropriately%20to%20the%20pursuit%20of%20excellence%20in%20this%20field.%20It%20is%20a%20blessing%20if%20you%20can%20find%20the%20right%20teacher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20for%20taking%20the%20time%20to%20share%20your%20insights%20and%20experiences%20with%20our%20readers!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAshutosh%20Kumar%20Thakur%20is%20a%20Bengaluru-based%20management%20professional%20and%20literary%20critic.%20He%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20ashutoshbthakur%40gmail.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693119285000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F27120348%2FSantosh-Kumar-Das-.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fmadhubani-art-the-most-rewarding-aspect-is-the-sense-of-belonging-it-gives-you-to-express-yourself%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20conversation%20with%20Ashutosh%20Kumar%20Thakur%2C%20a%20Bengaluru-based%20management%20professional%20and%20literary%20critic%2C%20Santosh%20Kumar%20Das%20speaks%20about%20his%20life%20and%20works.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A343%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fmadhubani-art-the-most-rewarding-aspect-is-the-sense-of-belonging-it-gives-you-to-express-yourself%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22M-cap%20of%203%20of%2010%20firms%20erodes%20by%20Rs%2082%2C082.91%20cr%2C%20Reliance%20biggest%20laggard%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693117983000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-04%2F23%2Ffull%2F1682249330-2022.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fm-cap-of-3-of-10-firms-erodes-by-rs-82-082-91-cr-reliance-biggest-laggard-123082700220_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20combined%2