its%20of%20hydroponics%20farming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EChanging%20the%20game%20for%20Indian%20farmers%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshwin%20points%20out%20that%20Indian%20farmers%20lack%20access%20to%20green%20fodder%20because%20it%20requires%20large%20tracts%20of%20land%20and%20gallons%20of%20water.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20states%20like%20Haryana%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20farmers%20already%20lack%20sufficient%20water%20for%20irrigation.%20If%20a%20farmer%20owns%20800%20cows%2C%20they%20have%20to%20reserve%2060%20acres%20of%20land%20to%20grow%20green%20fodder.%20That%20means%20they%20cannot%20grow%20any%20other%20crop%20on%20this%20land%2C%20which%20is%20not%20economical%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20with%20hydroponics%2C%20we%20can%20reduce%20the%20area%20and%20water%20requirements.%20With%20a%20one-tonne%20unit%20that%20can%20be%20installed%20in%20a%201%2C000-sq%20ft%20area%2C%20a%20farmer%20can%20save%20at%20least%20seven%20acres%20of%20land.%20This%20land%20can%20be%20utilised%20to%20grow%20other%20crops.%20Using%20hydroponics%2C%20farmers%20can%20harvest%20one%20kilo%20of%20green%20fodder%20by%20utilising%20just%201.5%20litres%20of%20water%20while%20saving%2099%20percent%20of%20the%20water%20required%20conventionally%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-1-1692278339.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ashwin%20helps%20farmers%20grow%20green%20fodder%20like%20maize%2C%20barley%2C%20wheat%20for%20goats%2C%20cows%2C%20buffaloes%2C%20ducks.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-1-1692278339.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F20